{"label":"News","id":"news-7","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"monsoon","type":"passage","label":"Is monsoon performance in June a cause for worry?","style":"big","data":{"title":"Is monsoon performance in June a cause for worry?","text":"The first month of the June-September monsoon season is almost over. How has the monsoon performed till now? The answer is important since India receives 75% of its annual rainfall during the southwest monsoon, which irrigates the water-intensive paddy crop. However, it may not rain as much this year because of El Nino, a cyclical warming of the equatorial Pacific Ocean that adversely affects monsoon rains. An HT analysis shows that the first month of the 2023 monsoon season has followed this expectation. However, it may not necessarily be a cause for worry yet as far as rice output is concerned."}},{"label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-2","data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"What is the importance of the monsoon season for India?","options":" It provides irrigation for water-intensive crops like paddy.\nIt supports the annual tourism industry.\nIt encourages outdoor recreational activities."},{"qText":"What is the typical timeframe for the southwest monsoon season in India?","options":"June-September\nDecember-February\nMarch-May"},{"qText":"What is El Niño?","options":"A cyclical warming of the equatorial Pacific Ocean.\nA phenomenon that causes heavy snowfall in mountainous regions.\nA geological process that leads to the formation of volcanoes."},{"qText":"How much of India's annual rainfall is received during the southwest monsoon?","options":"75%, 60%, 50%, 90%"},{"qText":"What does the HT analysis suggest about the performance of the 2023 monsoon season?","options":" It has been affected by El Niño.\nIt has been consistent with the average rainfall.\nIt has caused widespread flooding."},{"qText":"What is the potential impact of El Niño on monsoon rains?","options":"Decreased rainfall and drought conditions.\nIncreased rainfall and flooding.\nNo significant effect on rainfall patterns."},{"qText":"Should there be immediate concern about rice output based on the monsoon performance?","options":"It is too early to determine the impact on rice production.\nOther factors will compensate for any monsoon-related loss.\nIt has caused widespread flooding.\nYes, there may be a significant decrease in rice production.\nNo, rice output is unlikely to be affected."}]}},{"id":"monsson-g","type":"passage","label":"Glossary","data":{"title":"Glossary","text":[{"type":"html","text":"<b>Irrigate </b>: To supply water to crops or land to help growth.<br><br>\n<b>Monsoon</b>: A seasonal prevailing wind in the region of South and Southeast Asia, blowing from the southwest between May and September.<br><br>\n<b>Output</b>: The total amount of something that is produced.<br><br>\n<b>Paddy</b>: The cultivation of rice in a field where the soil is saturated with water.<br><br>\n<b>Adverse</b>: In a way that has a negative or harmful effect.<br><br>\n<b>Expectation</b>: The act of anticipating or looking forward to something.<br><br>\n<b>Annual</b>: Relating to a period of one year.<br><br>\n<b>Cyclical</b>: Happening or recurring in cycles."}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"monsoon-word","data":{"text":"To supply water to crops or land to help growth.|IRRIGATE\nA seasonal prevailing wind in the region of South and Southeast Asia, blowing from the southwest between May and September.|MONSOON\nThe total amount of something that is produced.|OUTPUT\nThe cultivation of rice in a field where the soil is saturated with water.|PADDY\nHappening or recurring in cycles.|CYCLICAL\nIn a way that has a negative or harmful effect.|ADVERSE\nThe act of anticipating or looking forward to something.|EXPECTATION\nRelating to a period of one year.|ANNUAL"}},{"id":"match","label":"Match: Synonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the synonym pairs.","text":"Flood, Deluge\nAnnual, Yearly\nIrrigate, Water\nPaddy, Rice field\nCyclical, Recurring\nAdversely, Negatively\nExpectation, Anticipation"}},{"id":"match-2","label":"Match: Antonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the antonym pairs.","text":"Flood, Drought\nAnnual, Occasional\nIrrigate, Dehydrate\nPaddy, Desert\nCyclical, Random\nAdversely, Positively\nExpectation, Surprise"}},{"id":"alcaraz","type":"passage","label":"Alcaraz becomes World No.1","style":"big","data":{"title":"Alcaraz becomes World No.1","text":"Carlos Alcaraz will return to world number one after beating Alex de Minaur 6-4, 6-4 on Sunday to win his first title on grass at Queen's Club. The Spaniard's fifth title of the season moves him back ahead of 23-time Grand Slam champion Novak Djokovic at the top of the rankings.\nAlcaraz was playing on the grass for just the third tournament of his career.\nThe 20-year-old has failed to get past the fourth round in two previous attempts at Wimbledon, but his impressive showing suggests he will be the biggest threat to Djokovic securing an eighth title at the All England Club next month. After battling past French lucky loser Arthur Rinderknech in the first round, Alcaraz did not drop a set in his final four matches at Queen's. De Minaur had dumped out Andy Murray and world number six Holger Rune on his route to the final.\nBut the Australian was left to rue Alcaraz's ability to win the big points in a tight contest.\nDe Minaur had two break points for the chance to serve for the first set when he led 4-3.\nAlcaraz responded, though, to hold serve and immediately break the world number 18 in the next game before serving out for the set. The US Open champion needed lengthy treatment between the two sets as he had strapping applied to his right quad. However, Alcaraz's movement did not seem affected as he again pounced with his only break point to move ahead 3-2 in the second set.\nTwo rare errors gave De Minaur some hope in the final game as Alcaraz found himself 0-30 down. But his booming serve dug him out of trouble as four straight points secured the new world number one title."}},{"label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-4","data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"Who did Carlos Alcaraz defeat to win his first title on grass at Queen's Club?","options":"Alex de Minaur, Andy Murray, Novak Djokovic, Holger Rune"},{"qText":"How many titles has Carlos Alcaraz won this season?","options":"5, 4, 3, 6"},{"qText":"Which Grand Slam tournament is Carlos Alcaraz aiming to perform better in?","options":"Wimbledon, Australian Open, French Open, US Open"},{"qText":"Who did Alex de Minaur defeat on his route to the final at Queen's Club?","options":"*Andy Murray, Novak Djokovic, Carlos Alcaraz, *Holger Rune"},{"qText":"How did Carlos Alcaraz respond when facing two break points at 4-3 down in the first set?","options":"He held serve\nHe was broken\nHe retired from the match\nHe won the first set"}]}},{"id":"alcarez-g","type":"passage","label":"Glossary","data":{"title":"Glossary","text":[{"type":"html","text":"<b>Top</b>: The highest position in the rankings.<br><br>\n<b>Threat</b>: A person or thing that poses a potential danger or challenge.<br><br>\n<b>Points</b>: Units used in tennis to determine game, set, or match progress.<br><br>\n<b>Booming</b>: Describing a serve with great power and force."}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"alcarez-word","data":{"text":"The highest position in the rankings.|TOP\nA person or thing that poses a potential danger or challenge.|THREAT\nUnits used in tennis to determine game, set, or match progress.|POINTS\nDescribing a serve with great power and force.|BOOMING"}},{"id":"match-3","label":"Match: Synonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the synonym pairs.","text":"Grass, Turf\nTop, Highest\nThreat, Danger\nPoints, Scores\nBooming, Thunderous"}},{"id":"match-4","label":"Match: Antonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the antonym pairs.","text":"Grass, Hardcourt\nTop, Bottom\nThreat, Safety\nBooming, Feeble"}},{"id":"woman","type":"passage","label":"Woman Electrocuted at New Delhi Railway Station","style":"big","data":{"title":"Woman Electrocuted at New Delhi Railway Station","text":" A woman was electrocuted after she touched an electric pole at New Delhi Railway Station while trying to walk through a flooded road on Sunday. The deceased has been identified as Sakshi Ahuja, a resident of east Delhi’s Preet Vihar. She reached the railway station on Sunday at 5.30 PM with her sister and three children to catch the Bhopal Shatabdi Express. However, outside the station, when she was crossing a waterlogged road, she held on to an electric pole for support and got electrocuted. The incident took place near exit gate number 1 of the station."}},{"label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-5","data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"Where did the incident of electrocution occur?","options":"New Delhi Railway Station, Preet Vihar, Bhopal Shatabdi Express, Waterlogged road"},{"qText":"What was the name of the woman who got electrocuted?","options":"Sakshi Ahuja, Bhopal Shatabdi Express, Preet Vihar"},{"qText":"How many children accompanied Sakshi Ahuja to the railway station?","options":"Three, Two, Four"},{"qText":"Why did Sakshi Ahuja touch the electric pole?","options":"She was trying to cross a waterlogged road.\nShe was attempting to climb the pole.\nShe wanted to check if it was electrified."},{"qText":"At which exit gate of the railway station did the incident occur?","options":"Gate number 1, Gate number 2, Gate number 3, Gate number 4"}]}},{"id":"rain-g","type":"passage","label":"Glossary","data":{"title":"Glossary","text":[{"type":"html","text":"<b>Resident</b>: A person who lives in a particular place.<br><br>\n<b>Support</b>: To provide assistance or hold up.<br><br>\n<b>Incident</b>:  A sudden and unexpected event.<br><br>\n<b>Waterlogged</b>: Completely covered or saturated with water."}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"rain-word","data":{"text":"A person who lives in a particular place.|RESIDENT\nTo provide assistance or hold up.|SUPPORT\nA sudden and unexpected event.|INCIDENT\nCompletely covered or saturated with water.|WATERLOGGED"}},{"id":"match-5","label":"Match: Synonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the synonym pairs.","text":"Electrocuted, Shocked\nResident, Inhabitant\nFlooded, Overflowing\nSupport, Assit\nIdentified, Recognized"}},{"id":"match-6","label":"Match: Antonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the antonym pairs.","text":"Electrocuted, Safe\nResident, Visitor\nFlooded, Dry\nSupport, Abandon\nIdentified, Unknown"}},{"id":"car","type":"passage","label":"Car Hits Autorikshaw, Two Critically Injured","style":"big","data":{"title":"Car Hits Autorikshaw, Two Critically Injured","text":"In a horrific incident, a speeding Lamborghini car rammed an auto-rickshaw in Delhi on Sunday. Two people were critically injured in the incident. According to the reports, a 24-year-old was driving the luxury car when it hit the auto on the Savitri Cinema flyover in south Delhi. The auto driver and his passenger — an engineer at IndiGo — have been hospitalized. \"They are not in a position to give a statement currently,\" police said. Disturbing visuals captured at the scene of the Delhi Lamborghini accident depict the auto-rickshaw in a mangled state, serving as a chilling reminder of the forceful impact. The luxury car involved in the collision also suffered significant damage, emphasizing the magnitude of the accident and the subsequent injuries caused. The police further added that Rajveer, the accused, has been detained and his medical examination is being done. \"His medical would confirm if he had consumed alcohol or not,\" police said. The car sustained damage due to the impact. However, the autorickshaw got mangled due to the incident. Prince Gautam, 31, was on his way to his office at the airport from his home east of Kailash when the accident happened around 7 am. Rajveer, the accused, has been detained and his medical examination is being done, police said. \"His medical would confirm if he had consumed alcohol or not,\" police said. The Delhi Lamborghini accident has sparked widespread public concern regarding road safety and the irresponsible behavior of some drivers on the city's streets."}},{"label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-6","data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"Who was driving the Lamborghini car during the accident in Delhi?","options":"Rajveer, Prince Gautam, An engineer at IndiGo"},{"qText":"Where did the accident take place in Delhi?","options":"Savitri Cinema flyover, East of Kailash, Near the airport, South Delhi streets"},{"qText":"How many people were critically injured in the incident?","options":"Two, Three, One"},{"qText":"What is the profession of the passenger in the auto-rickshaw?","options":"Engineer at IndiGo, Pilot, Auto driver"},{"qText":"What are the authorities waiting for before taking a statement from the injured victims?","options":"Completion of medical examination\nConsent from their families\nRecovery from injuries"},{"qText":"What is the public concern sparked by the Delhi Lamborghini accident?","options":"Road safety and irresponsible driver behavior\nTraffic congestion in Delhi\nEnvironmental impact of luxury cars"}]}},{"id":"car-g","type":"passage","label":"Glossary","data":{"title":"Glossary","text":[{"type":"html","text":"<b>Critical</b>: Severely injured or in a life-threatening condition.<br><br>\n<b>Rammed</b>: Collided forcefully.<br><br>\n<b>Mangled</b>:  Caused significant damage or distortion.<br><br>\n<b>Subsequent</b>: Following or coming after.<br><br>\n<b>Detained</b>: Arrested or held in custody.<br><br>\n<b>Irresponsible</b>: Reckless or not showing concern for consequences.<br><br>\n<b>Magnitude</b>: The size or extent of something."}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"car-word","data":{"text":"Severely injured or in a life-threatening condition.|CRITICAL\nCollided forcefully.|RAMMED\nCaused significant damage or distortion.|MANGLED\nThe size or extent of something.|MAGNITUDE\nFollowing or coming after.|SUBSEQUENT\nArrested or held in custody.|DETAINED\nReckless or not showing concern for consequences.|IRRESPONSIBLE"}},{"id":"match-7","label":"Match: Synonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the synonym pairs.","text":"Horrific, Terrible\nSpeeding, Racing\nIncident, Occurrence\nEmphasizing, Highlighting\nAccused, Suspected\nConfirm, Verify\nSparked, Ignited"}},{"id":"sweden","type":"passage","label":"1 Killed, Many Hurt as Roller Coaster Derails in Sweden Park","style":"big","data":{"title":"1 Killed, Many Hurt as Roller Coaster Derails in Sweden Park","text":"One person was killed and several others injured when a roller coaster derailed in Stockholm on Sunday, Swedish TV reported. Park officials told public broadcaster SVT that that one of the carriages on the Jetline rollercoaster derailed and fell to the ground at the Grona Lund amusement park.\"It is incredibly tragic and shocking,\" park spokeswoman Annika Troselius told SVT. \"Unfortunately we have been informed that one person is killed and many are injured.\" Police said seven people, both children and adults, were hospitalized after the accident. The amusement park was evacuated to facilitate the work of rescue crews. SVT reporter Jenny Lagerstedt, who was standing in line for another ride, said the carriage fell from a high altitude with passengers inside. \"Suddenly I heard a metallic thud and then the rides started to shake,\" she said. "}},{"label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-7","data":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions","questions":[{"qText":"What happened at Grona Lund amusement park in Stockholm?","options":"A roller coaster derailed\nThe park experienced a power outage\nAn animal escaped from the zoo"},{"qText":"How many people were reported to be killed in the roller coaster accident?","options":"One, None, Multiple, Exact number unknown"},{"qText":"What action was taken by the amusement park after the accident?","options":"The park was evacuated\nThe park was closed indefinitely\nAll rides at the park were halted temporarily"},{"qText":"What caused the roller coaster carriage to derail?","options":" The cause is yet to be determined\nMechanical failure\nHuman error\nExtreme weather conditions"}]}},{"id":"sweden-g","type":"passage","label":"Glossary","data":{"title":"Glossary","text":[{"type":"html","text":"<b>Derail</b>: To cause something to leave its tracks or intended course.<br><br>\n<b>Tragic</b>: Extremely sad, unfortunate, or distressing.<br><br>\n<b>Injured</b>: Physically harmed or wounded.<br><br>\n<b>Altitude</b>: The height above sea level or ground level.<br><br>\n<b>Evacuated</b>: To empty or remove people from a place of danger or emergency."}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"sweden-word","data":{"text":"To cause something to leave its tracks or intended course.|DERAIL\nExtremely sad, unfortunate, or distressing.|TRAGIC\nPhysically harmed or wounded.|INJURED\nTo empty or remove people from a place of danger or emergency.|EVACUATED\nThe height above sea level or ground level.|ALTITUDE"}},{"id":"match-8","label":"Match: Synonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the synonym pairs.","text":"Derail, Offtrack\nTragic, Sad\nShocking, Ashtonishing\nInjured, Hurt\nEvacuated, Emptied\nAltitude, Height"}},{"id":"match-9","label":"Match: Antonyms","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the antonym pairs.","text":"Derail, Ontrack\nTragic, Joyful\nShocking, Expected\nInjured, Unharmed\nEvacuated, Occupied\nAltitude, Depth"}}]}